description: A natural substance derived from living organisms such as cells, tissues, proteins, and DNA
A unique proper name or character sequence that identifies this particular material
A backup sequence of characters used to identify an entity
The type of biosample as characterized by its biological source material collected for testing, diagnostic, propagation, treatment or research purposes
If the biosample type is other, provide a description of the biosample.
An indication if the biosample is available (i.e., retained, available for use, etc.)

An examination that is performed to determine the extent of the spread of cancer based on histopathologic examination of one or more pathology specimens. Pathologic staging uses evidence acquired during the process of clinical staging, supplemented by histopathologic examination of surgical specimens.
The specific anatomical or biological region associated with a tissue or organ specimen.
Additional description on the anatomical or biological region associated with a tissue or organ specimen
The geographic location where biosample collection took place
The person or persons responsible for biosample collection
Date on which the material was collected

columnName: age group of individual at collection
description: A categorical value that groups this individual by age at the time of sample collection (e.g., "Adult", "18-24 years", etc.)
The age of the individual at the time of sample collection
One or more associations between the record and an organisation or institution.
Reference to the person from whom this material was collected.
A description of the procedures whereby biological samples for an experiment are sourced.
Date and time at which this material was listed or recorded officially, i.e. officially qualified or enrolled.
The conditions under which this biological material was stored.

A place on the Earth where this material is located, by its name or by its geographical location. This definition is intentionally vague to allow reuse locally (e.g. which freezer), for contacting (e.g. which institute), broadly for logistical or legal reasons (e.g. city, country or continent).
The date on which this material is no longer regarded as fit for use.
The percentage of tumor cells compared to total cells present in this material.
If applicable, a reference to a biosample that this material was derived from
An indication confirming that quality control processes were carried out and that the sequence did not meet the assessment criteria.
A reference to one or more files that contain information about this individual
A reference to one or more datasets that organises records for in a meaningful way (e.g., data releases, subpopulations, cohorts, etc.)
A written explanation, observation or criticism added to textual material.
